Documentation     Example of morse transmitter test
...
...               Change this example to use data driven style 
...               Test with different texts and speeds

Library           AtCommandLibrary.py
Library           String
Test Template     Send and verify output


*** Keywords ***
Verify echo
    [Arguments]    ${testing_data}
    Log To Console    \nTesting for "${testing_data}"
    Send text    ${testing_data}
    Response should be    AT+SEND="${testing_data}"


Send and verify output
    [Arguments]    ${testing_data}    ${expected_response}
    Verify echo    ${testing_data}
    Response should be    SENT="${expected_response}"
    Response should be    OK


*** Test Cases ***                ${testing_data}                                 ${expected_response}
#All small letters                 hello world                                     HELLO WORLD
#All capital letters               HELLO WORLD                                     HELLO WORLD
#All numbers                       145 789                                         145 789
#Letters + numbers                 Clb 4567 Z                                      CLB 4567 Z
#Long text                         Very very very long text                        VERY VERY VERY LONG TEXT
Other characters                   $&,,()!!!                                       XXXXXXXXX
Mixed combo                        HelLO26 wOrld!!! :)                             HELLO26 WORLDXXX XX


